# Intuition  
Largest component by size => Union by size
Shares common factor => we need to check all prime factors
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Make a hash table of integer , set.
In the hash table the key will be the array element (unique)
and value will be a set of all prime factors of it.
Then union each array elements with it's prime factors.

used sieve of eratosthenes to generate all prime factors in logn.
At first for each array elements size[element] = 1 and
size of all other numbers will be 0.  So after union size of prime factors will not be counted.


<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n * max number of prime factors among all nums[i]) + O(nlog(n))
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:   O( max( nums[ i ] ) )
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    int parent [];
    int size [];
    public int largestComponentSize(int[] nums) {
     int max = nums[0] ;
     HashMap<Integer,HashSet<Integer>> primeFactors = new HashMap<>();
     for(int val : nums)   max = Math.max(max,val);
     int seive [] = new int[max + 1];
     parent = new int[max + 1];
     size  = new int[max + 1];

     for(int i = 0; i < seive.length ; i++)   parent[i] = seive[i] = i;

     for(int i = 2; i*i < seive.length ; i++){
         if(seive[i] == i){
             for(int j = i; j < seive.length ; j+=i){
                 if(seive[j] == j) seive[j] = i;
             }
         }
     }

     for(int i = 0; i < nums.length ; i++){
         int val = nums[i];
         size[val] = 1;
         HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();
        addFactors(val,seive,set);
         primeFactors.put(val,set);
     }




         for(int val : nums){
             for(int fac : primeFactors.get(val)){
             if(val % fac == 0){
                 if(findparent(fac) != findparent(val)) {
                  union(fac , val);
                 }
             }
         }
         }



            int ans = 1;
            for(int val : size) {
                ans = Math.max(ans,val);
            }
            return ans;


    }

    public int findparent(int node){
         if(parent[node] == node) return node;
         return parent[node] = findparent(parent[node]);
    }

    public void union(int u , int v){
      u = findparent(u);
      v = findparent(v);
      if(size[u] > size[v]){
          parent[v] = u;
          size[u]+=size[v];
      }else {
        parent[u] = v;
          size[v]+=size[u];
      }
    }

    public void addFactors(int val, int seive [] , HashSet<Integer> set){
          while(val > 1){
              set.add(seive[val]);
              val = val/seive[val];
          }
    }
}
